Alice stood by the edge of the lake, the soft glow of the moonlight dancing upon the rippling water. She gently dipped her toes in the cool liquid, letting it caress her skin like a gentle lover. The sensation was both soothing and bittersweet, reminding her of the world she had left behind, forever suspended in time.
"Salut tu m'a manqué," the stranger said, breaking her trance. She turned to face him
